Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed, white and green parts separated). Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together scallion greens, apple, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} (save the rest for later), a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a large pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to marinate.

Tear @pulled chicken{8%ounce} into smaller, bitesized pieces. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken, scallion whites, @chipotle powder{1/4%tsp} (we'll use the rest later), and a large pinch of salt. Toss to combine. Cook until chicken is warmed and starting to crisp at edges, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir @water{1/4%cup}, remaining @white wine vinegar{4%tsp}, @adobo sauce{1%ounce}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1} into pan with chicken. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is thick and coats meat, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, a pinch of @chipotle powder{1/8%tsp}, @water{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Taste and add more chipotle if you like it spicy. Split @brioche buns{2} in half.

> Enjoy a toasty bun? Toast the split buns in a toaster or in a 425 degree oven for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Spread chipotle crema on cut side of buns, then fill buns with chicken and a little bit of slaw. Serve with remaining slaw on the side.

> Delicious pulled chicken sandwiches in just 20 minutes? Yep! We make it happen with precooked pulled chicken—all you have to do is heat it in a pan and you're at tender, juicy bliss. To keep things fresh, there's also an apple carrot slaw, plus a spiced chipotle sour cream for smoky intrigue.